name: Great Value apple juice recall
summary: Walmart has issued a voluntary recall of its Great Value Apple Juice 6-packs sold in 25 states due to elevated arsenic levels. The recall affects 64-ounce containers with a "best by" date of February 2024. The FDA has warned that arsenic levels exceeding the standard can cause adverse health effects, particularly in children. Affected states include Alabama, Arkansas, California, Colorado, Florida, Georgia, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Kentucky, Louisiana, Michigan, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri, Nebraska, New Mexico, North Carolina, Ohio, Oklahoma, South Carolina, Tennessee, Texas, Virginia, and Wisconsin. Walmart advises consumers to discard or return the recalled product for a full refund. The source of the arsenic contamination is still under investigation.

name: Massachusetts mosquito virus
summary: Massachusetts communities are facing a significant threat from a rare and deadly mosquito-borne virus known as Eastern Equine Encephalitis (EEE). The virus, which can cause severe brain inflammation and even death, has put several towns at high risk. Authorities are urging residents to take precautions, including avoiding outdoor activities at dusk and dawn when mosquitoes are most active. Parks and fields have been closed at night in some affected areas, and residents are encouraged to use insect repellent and wear protective clothing when outdoors. Health officials are monitoring the situation closely and providing updates as the threat level changes.
